FBIS4-60540 "drnes102_l_94004" FBIS-NES-94-102 Daily Report 26 May 1994 ISRAEL Shahal: 'Arafat Needs Invitation To Visit Jerusalem Shahal: 'Arafat Needs Invitation To Visit Jerusalem TA2605102694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 26 May 94 TA2605102694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Minister Moshe Shahal says that Yasir 'Arafat will not be able to visit Jerusalem without an official Israeli invitation, because a person fulfilling a political role cannot visit a foreign country without an invitation. According to Minister Shahal the incidents between Israelis and Palestinian policemen over the last few days stem from a lack of coordination between the Israeli authorities and the Palestinian police. This is reported by our correspondent Dani Gur-Arye.
